<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.48.20-21_0001a" />

<note type="curatorial">418-1</note>

<opener>
<dateline>April 18, '66</dateline>


<salute>Dear Lucile,</salute>
</opener>
<p>I've been re-reading your letter of March 8, and it makes me happy. I'm especially pleased with what you say of the <hi rend="underline">Messiah</hi> and the <hi rend="double underline">way you say it</hi> &#8212; "its own music", "luminous beauty" etc.</p>

<p>I'm writing this merely to say hello to all of you there that you may know I'm thinking of you with affection.</p>

<p>Two weeks from Wednesday I'll be 

<pb facs="nei.j4c.48.20-21_0001b"/>
<fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>

running over to the <hi rend="caps">U</hi> of Kansas. Immediately afterwards I'll run into Vermillion for four or five days at the <hi rend="caps">U.</hi> of <hi rend="caps">S. D.</hi>.</p>
  
<p>Did I tell you that Bancroft has made the first Sunday in August "Neihardt Day"? And they are working on a Black Elk pageant to be given every year on that day. The 16 horsemen will be only a relatively small <del>pa</del> part of the show, I understand.</p>

<p>I do too like you'ns!!</p>
<closer>
&#8212; <signed>John N.</signed>
</closer>

<note><del>S<unclear/></del></note>

